<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-20T08:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-20T08:34:00-05:00" n="579" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1150: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-20T22:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">October 20,
                                        1919, 10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 22, 12:06
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Practically all original members of Service Corps including <persName corresp="#p_ECGH1">Emerson</persName> declare that they are done and
                            will leave for the United States and ask to be relieved quickly. They
                            all declare with truth they enlisted for the war and have served a year
                            after close away <pb facs="0647" n="535" xml:id="pg_535"/> from families
                            and at pecuniary loss, that their efforts are useless under existing
                            arrangement, their instructions and orders are in every way ignored by
                            officials of the railways. …</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>